  "prompt": "What are the similarities and differences between Buddhism and Jainism?",
  "response": "Here's a comparison of Buddhism and Jainism:\n\nSimilarities:\n1. Indian origin\n2. Founded around the same time (6th-5th century BCE)\n3. Reject the caste system\n4. Emphasize non-violence (ahimsa)\n5. Believe in karma and rebirth\n6. Seek liberation from the cycle of suffering\n7. Practice meditation\n8. Reject ritualistic practices of Vedic Hinduism\n9. Criticize the authority of Vedas\n10. Teach ethical living and compassion\n\nDifferences:\n1. Founders:\n- Buddhism: Founded by Siddhartha Gautama\n- Jainism: Founded by Mahavira\n\n2. Concept of God:\n- Buddhism: Non-theistic\n- Jainism: Also non-theistic, but believes in spiritual beings\n\n3. Soul concept:\n- Buddhism: Denies permanent soul (anatta)\n- Jainism: Believes in eternal soul\n\n4. Ascetic practices:\n- Buddhism: Middle path, moderate asceticism\n- Jainism: Extreme asceticism\n\n5. Approach to suffering:\n- Buddhism: Eliminate desire\n- Jainism: Complete detachment\n\n6. Philosophical emphasis:\n- Buddhism: Mindfulness and mental discipline\n- Jainism: Absolute non-violence and self-control\n\nBoth offer distinct paths to spiritual liberation.",
